welcome_message_body: "Welcome to Silverdale, a charming city known for its scenic beauty and vibrant community. We invite you to explore all that our city has to offer and hope you enjoy your stay in our unique corner of the United States."

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Bremerton Airport is a small and efficient building that serves both commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: Private Terminal
terminals.description: The private terminal at Bremerton Airport provides a more exclusive and luxurious experience for private flights.

wifi.note: Complimentary WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Kenmore Air Harbor SPB Airport serves as the hub for all flights and passenger services.

terminals.name: Seaplane Terminal
terminals.description: The seaplane terminal at Kenmore Air Harbor SPB Airport caters to seaplane flights and offers a unique and scenic travel experience.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport for all passengers.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Boeing Field/King County International Airport handles all commercial and private flights.

terminals.name: North Terminal
terminals.description: The North Terminal at Boeing Field/King County International Airport is primarily used for cargo and general aviation flights.

wifi.note: Free WiFi is available throughout the airport.

terminals.name: Main Terminal
terminals.description: The main terminal at Snohomish County - Paine Field Airport offers a variety of amenities for travelers, including dining options, retail stores, and rental car services.

terminals.name: North Terminal
terminals.description: The North Terminal at Snohomish County - Paine Field Airport primarily serves private and charter flights, with limited amenities available for passengers.

wifi.note: Passengers can connect to the airport's free WiFi network by selecting 'Paine Field WiFi' from their device's list of available networks.
